    <thetext>The spec for Math.trunc(x) does not explicitly state that:

* If x is greater than 0 and less than 1, the result is +0.
* If x is greater than -1 and less than 0, the result is -0.

(I filed this because the spec is otherwise very explicit about positive and negative zeros.)</thetext>
